Partial. Sentencing After Revocation, Sentencing Hearing held on May 18, 2015. Judge Boles presiding.
(Original kept in 10CF72)

Defendant Joshua L. Stofferahn in Court with Attorney Daniel P Repka.  ADA William H. Thorie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  PO Tricia Gilby present.  Includes Sentencing on Revocation on 10CF72 and Plea/Sentencing on 15CF47.  Cases called at 4:25 p.m.  Court notes familiarity with Defendant from DC.  Defendant does not wish to substitute Judge.  Court questions review of Revocation Order and Warrant.  Atty. Repka notes correction as to allegation vs. omission.  Atty. Repka presents Plea Questionnaire on 15CF47.  ADA Thorie informs Court of recommendation of concurrent sentence on 15CF47.  Court informs Defendant of charges, possible penalties and rights.  Court advises of restriction as to voting and firearms with felony conviction.  Defendant understands and pleads Guilty to Count One of 15CF47.  Court finds that Defendant has freely, voluntarily and knowingly waived rights and entered plea.  Court accepts plea and adjudicates.  ADA Thorie makes recommendations as to 10CF72 for 4 years; 2 years initial confinement and 2 years extended supervision.  ADA Thorie notes that time Defendant has served is 555 days so he believes that Defendant has 175 days left of confinement and then 2 years ES.  Conditions of ES requested are a no drink provision, AODA and other programming as recommended by COMPAS, association restrictions, noting Randy Meyer.  Court questions.  ADA Thorie is requesting sentence withheld on 15CF47 and 2 years probation, concurrent w/15CF47.  Court adjourns for Atty. Repka to speak with Defendant.  Recall at 4:53 p.m.  Atty. Repka makes statement.  ADA Thorie responds and notes jail credit and intention of recommendation.  Court questions Defendant, he understands and wishes to go forward with sentencing.  Atty. Repka makes statement and recommendation, requests time served, County confinement if needed.  Defendant declines statement.  Court notes that Defendant successfully completed PC DC program.  Court notes that there are no programs in County Jail vs. programs they have in prison.  Court notes factors and considerations.  Court sentences Defendant.  On 10CF72: On  Count One, sentenced to 4 years in prison; 2 years initial confinement and 2 years extended supervision.  On Count Two 4 years, concurrent to Count One.  Conditions of ES are those conditions set by Agent but sets two specific conditions of no possession or consumption of alcohol or non-prescription medication or illegal drugs.  Only prescription medications as prescribed and in amounts presecribled.  Any AODA treatment as needed.  If Agent rquests additional treatment, Defendant should comply.  Agent has discretion of supervision.  No contact w/drug users, specifically Randy Meyer.  Court grants credit for 556 days granted.  On 15CF47 Court witholds sentence and orders 2 years probation, concurrent to two counts in 10CF72.  Conditions of probation the same as those in Extended Supervision.  DNA surcharge ordered and sample if required.  Court costs.  Court advises of appeal rights.
